## Loot Modifier

A mod to allow datapacks to modify existing loot tables

Loot table modifiers should be defined in <code>data/<namespace>/lootmodifier/loot_table_modifier/<name>.json</code>

## JSON Format

<code>target</code>: A loot table identifier, or list of loot table identifiers, to modify.

<code>pools</code>: A list of pools to add to the loot tables. Uses vanilla [loot pool format](https://minecraft.wiki/w/Loot_table#Pool).

## Example

Gives dirt and grass blocks a 10% chance to drop a diamond when mined
<pre>
{
  "target": [
    "minecraft:blocks/dirt",
    "minecraft:blocks/grass_block"
  ],
  "pools": [
    {
      "conditions": [
        {
          "condition": "minecraft:random_chance",
          "chance": 0.1
        }
      ],
      "entries": [
        {
          "type": "minecraft:item",
          "name": "minecraft:diamond"
        }
      ],
      "rolls": 1.0
    }
  ]
}
</pre>
